For several years bariatric surgery proved effective for the treatment of type 2 diabetes, but the main studies were conducted among people with morbidly obese, having a body mass index (BMI) of 35 or higher.
BMI, a measure of weight relative to height, is considered normal if from 18.5 to 24.9.
A BMI of 25 or above suggests that a person is overweight, and those with a BMI above 30 are people with obesity.
