Xi Jinping calls to do more open to the world economy
The economy must become more open to the world, to boost its growth, as President Xi Jinping said Tuesday in a speech to the group, faces the task of management reforms.
"China must focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop a policy of openness," he said, referring to the participants of the 16th Central Committee meeting of the leading group on comprehensive deepening of reform.
According to him, the expansion of openness and economic reforms will give new impetus and vitality and provide new space for economic development.
The leading group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation of investor access to the market, changing the rules of border control, the promotion of state-owned enterprises (SOE), attracting private capital and review of the registration system.
According to the statement, will be compiled a list of sectors of the economy and production, unavailable for investment.
The system will be debugged gradually through pilot programs.
This is an important step because it will give the market a more significant role in the allocation of resources, ensure the rule of law in the field of business and increase the openness, the statement said.
The government also will weaken the control of the powers granted to them, thereby ensuring that companies themselves will conduct their business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to strengthen local growth.
Even more areas will be available for private investors to increase the openness of state-dominated sectors of the economy.
"the government will not change its policy toward foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, as well as to provide them with the best conditions," - said in a statement.
In addition to facilitate the procedure for submitting applications for permanent residence permit for foreigners, or "greencard" by optimizing and simplifying the process of filing requirements.
The meeting also discussed the rights of lawyers and questions of professional training of prosecutors and judges.
According to an official report issued after the meeting, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and Liu and Zhang Yunshan Gaoli ministers.
